<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-02-26T18:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-02-26T18:35:00-05:00" n="87" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                        <head>87. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency
                                Station in Saigon</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                                State</gloss><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d87fn1">Source:
                                Department of State, Central Files, 751K.00/2-2662. Secret; Flash;
                                Critic. Also sent to the Director of NSA. Received at 8 p.m.,
                                February 26.</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="italic">Saigon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-02-27T07:35:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">February 27,
                                        1962—7:35 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>262335Z. Between 2 or 3 aircraft attacked Presidential Palace at 0715
                            local. Guards responded with anti-aircraft fire by 0730 local. Extent of
                            damage unknown.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>